main event: Several observers reported seeing 3-4 objects above the horizon at approx. 27N 155-27W on September 9, 1963.
interesting points: The sighting occurred over a duration of 5 minutes, The objects were initially thought to be burning stars, but the duration of the sighting was too long for this assumption, The weather conditions were reported as clear, An Airman named Robert F. Havens was involved in the report, A separate sighting by Hawaiian Airlines No. 9332 noted a greenish blue burning object at a similar location.
